<HEADLINE> Brazil Installs First Environmental Court </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fernando David Fonseca Gonzalves, Brazil's first environmental
judge, said that although the court right now has a small
structure, of barely five people, it's question of a pioneering
initiative showing that justice does care about the environment,
and that specializing will guarantee processes' alertness.
</P>
<P>
The judge said that this court's creation means the presence of
Federal Justice in an area that is the doorway to El Pananal, the
world's biggest swamp, and where Brazil shares the border with two
countries (Bolivia and Paraguay).
</P>
<P>
This initiative's success can lead to the establishing of other
courts of this specialty.  
</P>
