<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 13-Year-Old Indicted as Adult in Teacher's Slaying in U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
If convicted, Nathaniel Brazill will get life in prison without
parole.
</P>
<P>
The boy could be held only until he turned 21 if he had been
prosecuted as a juvenile.
</P>
<P>
Nathaniel was charged in the May 26 slaying of Lake Worth
Community Middle School teacher Barry Grunow, who was killed in
the closing minutes of the last day of the school year.
</P>
<P>
The incident was the latest act of violence in a U.S. school
after a spate of mass school shootings in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Nathaniel's lawyer, Richard Udell, has said the gun
accidentally went off when the boy pulled it out. He said the
fault lies with the .25-caliber gun the boy stole from his
grandfather's house days before.
</P>
<P>
The boy, a musician with perfect attendance and dreams of
becoming a Secret Service agent for the president, is being held
in a juvenile detention center.
</P>
<P>
State Attorney Barry Krischer publicly called for adult charges
against the boy.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, protesters decrying the expected indictment marched
around the Palm Beach County Courthouse in Florida, banging on
bongo drums and shaking tambourines. When the indictment was
handed up, they gathered in a hallway outside the courtroom and
sang the civil rights anthem "We Shall Overcome." 
</P>
</TEXT>
