<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania, Macedonia to Cooperate in Road Transport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Romanian Prime Minister Mugur
Isarescu and his Macedonian counterpart Ljubco Georgievski signed
here on Monday an Agreement regarding road transport.
</P>
<P>
Georgievski arrived in Bucharest on Monday for a two-day
official visit, at the invitation of his Romanian counterpart
Mugur Isarescu.The visit is the first by Macedonia's Premier to
Romania.
</P>
<P>
According to the official Rompres news agency, the conclusion
of the Agreement regarding road transport is part of the policy of
liberalization of the road transport based on free competition
among road operators, with reduced intervention by the state in
regulating this form of transport.
</P>
<P>
The agreement is in line with the targets of the National
Strategy for Romania's preparation for admission to the European
and Atlantic structures, including the legal framework of the
bilateral cooperation, considering the pace of the development of
the political and economic ties between Romania and the other
states.
</P>
<P>
A new road agreement appeared as necessary due to the economic
and political interests of Romania and to the pace of the
development of the Romanian-Macedonian relations.
</P>
<P>
On the same day, the two prime ministers also signed a
convention on double taxation and tax evasion. The convention will
apply to residents in Romania and Macedonia and will comprise the
income tax,taxes on revenues from stocks and shares as well as
real estate transactions, wage taxes and capital increase taxes.
</P>
</TEXT>
