Gonzalez Macchi, suspended attending the summit, because of his
country's internal problems. In his place, Foreign Relations
Minister Juan Esrteban Aguirre, will participate in the event.
</P>
<P>
At Group of Rio's summit, leaders will approve several
documents prepared by technical delegates and Foreign Ministers
on June 12,13 and 14, and at the meeting's end will sign a joint
statement.
</P>
<P>
Heads of State and Government of Group of Rio have met up every
year since 1987 to strengthen political and economic relations
between countries of Latin America and the Caribbean.
</P>
<P>
The group's First summit Meeting took place on November 29,
1987 in Acapulco, Mexico, with the participation of Presidents of
Argentina, Brazil, Panama, Peru, Colombia, Mexico, Venezuela and
Uruguay, members of Group of Eight.  
</P>
</TEXT>
