<HEADLINE> S. Africa to Improve Its International Image </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 12 (Xinhua) -- South Africa is to embark on
a special marketing drive to improve the country's international
image, Deputy Foreign Affairs Minister Aziz Pahad said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Pahad said six ministries, namely Foreign Affairs, Trade and
Industry, Finance, Environmental Affairs and Tourism, Arts,
Culture, Science and Technology and the Ministry in the
Presidency, will form an inter- ministerial committee in charge of
the image campaign.
</P>
<P>
A panel of between 20 and 25 people from outside the government
is also being set up to advise the ministerial committee.
</P>
<P>
The Government Communication and Information Service will
coordinate the program.
</P>
<P>
This is not about promoting the government but to market South
Africa as a whole in a collective image-building drive, Pahad
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
