delegation. On Monday he also held talks with Iranian Commerce
Minister Mohammad Shariatmadari, Iranian Oil Minister Bijan Namdar
Zanganeh and Iranian Minister of Culture and Islamic Guidance
Ataollah Mohajerani.
</P>
<P>
The talks focused on expansion of relations in oil, energy,
industry, tourism, trade, service, investment and air
transportation fields.
</P>
<P>
Rolandis and Mohajerani also signed a letter of understanding to
develop cooperation in tourism industry.
</P>
<P>
The agreement calls for easing the regulations on exchange of
tourists and encouraging tourist agencies from the two countries to
hold arts festivals, sports events and exhibitions to bring about
close contacts between the two nations. 
</P>
