<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The participation of Palestinian
leader Yasser Arafat in the funeral of the late Syrian President
Hafez al-Assad will open a new chapter in bilateral relations, a
Palestinian minister said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Al-Assad died of a heart attack on Saturday. Arafat arrived in
Cairo earlier Monday en route to Damascus to take part in al-
Assad's funeral, scheduled to take place on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Arafat's participation is a sign to demonstrate the appreciation
of the long-standing relations binding the Palestinians and Syria,
Minister of Parliamentary Affairs Nabil Amr was quoted as saying by
Egypt's Middle East News Agency.
</P>
<P>
It has been widely maintained that Arafat and al-Assad had tense
relations due to Palestinians' signing of peace accords with Israel
unilaterally. Damascus hosts several hardline factions of the
Palestine Liberation Organization, of which Arafat is the chairman.
</P>
<P>
But Amr said the Palestinian-Syrian relations have never been
tense.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he expressed confidence that Arafat's visit to Syria
will afford an opportunity to forge a new relationship with al-
Assad's successor, his son, Bashar.
</P>
<P>
Bashar has been promoted to the commander-in-chief of the armed
forces and nominated for the presidency.
</P>
<P>
Arafat last visited Syria in 1996. 
</P>
