<HEADLINE> Two S. African Opposition Parties to Cooperate in Local Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The South African opposition
Democratic Party (DP) leader Tony Leon said Monday it was possible
for the New National Party (NNP) to consider his party's proposals
on cooperation in the November local government elections.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued after a meeting with NNP leader Marthinus
van Schalkwyk, Leon warned, however, that the DP was not prepared
to change the basis of the agreement between the parties in the
Western Cape coalition government.
</P>
<P>
Their talks followed a DP federal council proposal on Sunday
that the NNP fight the poll under the DP banner.
</P>
<P>
Van Schalkwyk rejected this as "either extreme arrogance or
politically naive", and the NNP also threatened to reduce the
number of DP members in the Western Cape cabinet.
</P>
<P>
Leon said his talks with Van Schalkwyk were conducted in a
"positive atmosphere".
</P>
<P>
"I expect that the NNP will table a response to the DP proposal
and this will be considered," he said.
</P>
<P>
"I believe it is possible for the DP and the NNP to take
further the proposals made yesterday at the DP federal council,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
The DP, however, remained totally committed to consolidating
the opposition in South Africa and would continue to work toward
this goal, he said.
</P>
<P>
The DP has four out of 12 members in the coalition cabinet in
Western Cape.
</P>
<P>
Leon said on Sunday that the best way to ensure that democracy
worked was to build an opposition that could bring the ruling
African National Congress below 50 percent of the vote.
</P>
<P>
"It makes no sense for the DP and the NNP to continue fighting
for the support of opposition voters. It is time to put South
Africa first," Leon said.
</P>
<P>
The DP was recognized as the leading opposition party by South
Africans from across the political spectrum.
</P>
<P>
"It makes no sense to give up this clear identity and our
sharply defined message of strong, effective and principled
opposition. It is thus the DP's duty to lead the consolidation of
the opposition," he said. 
</P>
