<HEADLINE> Share Prices End Flat on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) slipped 0.55 points to
end at 2,042.06 points in thin dealings.
</P>
<P>
The total volume merely amounted to 214.31 million shares worth
414.60 million Singapore dollars (about 240.72 million U.S.
dollars). There were 137 advances against 173 decliners with 231
counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The larger block was the 14.88 million parcel by Ossia Int'l
which was transacted at 0.925 Singapore dollars per share. it was
followed by the FHTK which had 10.92 million units done. Brierley
was the next with 6.59 million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
PacCent clinched to the top gainer as it surged up 140 cents to
close at 18.30 Singapore dollars. Creative 50 gained 60 cents
finishing the day at 49.00 Singapore dollars. DBS edged up 30
cents to end at 21.50 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
SIA and SIA 200 led losers of the day sinking 60 cents each to
close both at 17.20 Singapore dollars. SPH and SPH 100 shed 50
cents to finish at 28.70 and 28.60 Singapore dollars respectively.
Venture retreated 30 cents to end at 18.30 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Local TV broadcast quoted brokers as saying that a mixed
performance by Wall Street on Friday dampened investors appetite
for bargain hunting although bank and property shares managed to
garner buying interest. 
