<HEADLINE> 061252fff International Workshop on Small, Medium-sized Enterprises Opens in Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 12 (Xinhua) -- An international workshop on small
and medium-sized enterprises with an attendance of over 70
participants from Latin America and Africa opened in the Kenyan
capital Nairobi on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The three-day workshop, sponsored by the Kenyan government, the
Latin America Economic System (SELA) and the U. N. Development
Program, is expected to analyze the achieved experience in making
sound industrial policies for small and medium-sized enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The workshop, the first of its kind in Kenya, is a result of a
previous visit by a SELA delegation to Kenya in May 1999 to
explore possibilities of promoting cooperation between Latin
American countries and the African continent.
</P>
<P>
"This is a critical conference for Kenya, which will boost the
country's industrial transformation and poverty eradication,"
said Kenya's Minister for Planning Gideon Okemo when officially
opening the workshop.
</P>
<P>
SELA, a regional inter-governmental organization, groups 28
Latin American and Caribbean countries with an aim to promote
economic cooperation between its member states.
</P>
<P>
Small and medium-sized enterprises employ about 61 percent of
labor force in Kenya and contribute to 18 percent of the country's
gross domestic product, according to the Labor and Human Resource
Development Ministry. 
</P>
