traveling with President Kim Dae-jung to Pyongyang Tuesday for a
historic summit said Monday they hope the talks will create a
foundation for the North and South of the Korean Peninsula to cope
with the tragedy of national division.
</P>
<P>
However, they cautioned that people should not expect too much
from the forthcoming summit between Kim Dae-jung and Kim Jong Il,
leader of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
</P>
<P>
