<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Senior CPC Official Meets Indonesian Guests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Wei Jianxing, a Standing Committee
member of the Political Bureau of the Communist Party of China (
CPC) Central Committee, met with an Indonesian delegation of
leaders of Islamic parties led by Aisyaah Aminy here today.
</P>
<P>
Wei, also a member of the Secretariat of the CPC Central
Committee, stressed that the CPC hopes to conduct new exchanges
and cooperation with all major Indonesian parties on the basis of
the principles of independence, absolute equality, mutual respect
and non-interference into each other's internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
Wei hailed the friendship between China and Indonesia.
Indonesia is one of the earliest countries to establish diplomatic
ties with China, and the two countries were both advocates of the
Bandung Asian-African Conference, he added.
</P>
<P>
During his visit to China in December last year, Indonesian
President Abdurrahman Wahid and Chinese President Jiang Zemin
reached consensus and understanding over the establishment of good-
neighborly bilateral ties of mutual-trust featuring comprehensive
cooperation, Wei said.
</P>
<P>
In May this year, both foreign ministers signed a joint
statement concerning bilateral cooperation in the future, paving
the way for the development of bilateral ties of mutual interest
and cooperation, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Wei pointed out that both China and Indonesia are important
developing countries. The development of friendly cooperative ties
between the two countries is not only in the fundamental interests
of both peoples, but also beneficial to peace and stability in the
region and the world as well.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government appreciates the Indonesian government's
position on the issue of Taiwan and human rights, he added, hoping
that both countries will enhance friendly cooperation and be good
neighbors and good friends forever.
</P>
<P>
Aminy praised the achievements China has made since it
initiated reforms and opening up twenty years ago, indicating that
the achievements would have been impossible without the forceful
leadership of the CPC.
</P>
<P>
Aminy also highly valued the principles the CPC advocates in
governing party-to-party relations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
