<HEADLINE> India's Industry Grows by 12.2 Percent in April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
According to quick estimates of Index of Industrial Production
released by the Central Statistical Organisation Monday, the
manufacturing sector grew by 14 percent in April 2000 as against 5.
7 percent in the same month last year.
</P>
<P>
Other sectors which contributed to high industrial growth
during the month were mining sector growing at 5.2 percent as
against negative 2 percent last year and electricity which grew at
3.2 percent compared to 6 percent in April 1999.
</P>
<P>
The country's industry production grew by 8 percent in the 1999-
2000 fiscal year as against 3.9 percent recorded in 1998-1999.
</P>
