<HEADLINE> Pakistan to Check Price hike </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The Pakistani government is
considering on a comprehensive law to effectively check
unreasonable price hike and dismantle monopolies and cartels to
protect the consumer interests, the Associated Press of Pakistan (
APP) reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The new law, initially drafted by the Monopoly Control
Authority (MCA), is presently being considered by the government
with some changes and improvements to make it further effective,
sources from the MCA said.
</P>
<P>
According to the sources, the proposed law envisages stiff
penalties and other punishments, besides, foolproof arrangements
to discourage unfair trade practices both n public and private
sectors.
</P>
<P>
The new law will empower the Monopoly Control Authority to take
cognizance of price escalation in different areas including
pharmaceutical, cement, automobiles and items of daily use, the
sources said. 
</P>
