<HEADLINE> HK Stocks Drop Slightly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The benchmark Hang Seng Index of
Hong Kong stocks fell 65.21 points, or 0.40 percent, to close at
16,055.05 points Monday amid sluggish trading.
</P>
<P>
Most investors were sidelined, awaiting U.S. economic data
later this week that should provide more indications on the
direction of interest rates, analysts said.
</P>
<P>
Turnover was 8.968 billion HK dollars (1.150 billion U.S.
dollars), compared with Friday's 9.078 billion HK dollars (1.164
billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Of the four sub-indices of Hang Seng Index, Finance, Utilities
and Commerce and Industry lost 0.06 percent, 0.21 percent and 0.80
percent, respectively, while properties picked up 0.43 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng China Enterprises Index and the Hang Seng China-
Affiliated Corp Index went up 0.21 percent and 0.16 percent,
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng IT Index rose 0.60 percent and the Hang Seng IT
Portfolio Index went up 2.25 percent.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong stocks opened at 16,125.75 Monday, up 5.49 points or
0.03 percent, and climbed 23.46 points, or 0.15 percent, to close
the morning session at 16,143.72. 
</P>
</TEXT>
