fly to Damascus later Monday to attend the funeral of his Syrian
counterpart Hafez al-Assad, Egyptian officials said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Assad died of heart attack at the age of 69 on Saturday. A state
funeral for him is slated for Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak, who received military training with Assad in the former
Soviet Union in the 1960s, declared three days of official mourning
following the announcement of the Syrian president's death.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak pledged his support to Assad's son and heir apparent
Bashar al-Assad in a telephone call late Sunday, Egypt's Middle
East News Agency reported overnight.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak expressed his condolences over the passing of Assad. He
stressed Egypt's backing to Bashar and Syria, wishing him success
in continuing the march initiated by his late father.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian president had earlier sent a telegram of support to
Bashar shortly after he was nominated as a candidate for the
presidency by the ruling Baath party and promoted to commander-in-
chief of the armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak held an emergency cabinet meeting early Sunday to
discuss the situation in Syria after Assad's death. He told
reporters after the meeting that Egypt supports the coming
leadership in Syria.
</P>
<P>
"We respect the Syrian people's way of choosing their president
and wish Syria stability and security because it is a pivotal
country" in the region, he said. 
