<HEADLINE> Nepali Film Festival to Be Held in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The 3rd Nepal Motion Picture
Award and Nepali Film Festival will be held here on July 7-9, the
Radio Nepal reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
A total of 34 of the best Nepali movies released between
January 1, 1997 to mid-April, 2000 will compete for 27 different
awards, including Best Film, Best Male and Female Actors and Best
Song, among others, the radio said.
</P>
<P>
Foreign film producers and film artists, including Indian
actress Jaya Pradha and Pooja Batra as well as Bangladeshi actress
Rojina,will also attend the festival, it said.
</P>
<P>
The event is being organized with the aim to uplift Nepali art
and culture, honor the film artists and promote international
cultural relations, the radio quoted organizers as saying.
</P>
<P>
Rallies and seminars regarding improving Nepalese film industry
will be held on the occasion and even the nominated films will be
shown in movie halls of major cities, according to the organizers.
</P>
<P>
The festival, to be held after a gap of more than two years, is
co-organized by Nepal Motion Picture Association and Nepal Film
Producers' Association. 
