<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Madagascar Becomes Thailand's New Fishery Source </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Thailand and Madagascar have
agreed to cooperate in fishery, making the island state in the
Indian Ocean a new fishing site for Thai trawlers, a senior
official of the Thai Agriculture and Cooperatives Ministry said
here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Dhammarong Prakobboon, director-general of fishery department,
was quoted by Thailand News Agency as saying that the agreement
was signed during a recent meeting here between Thai Agriculture
Minister Prabhatra Pothisuthon and Madagascar's fishery minister.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreement, Thai trawlers can fish in the
territorial waters of Madagascar and a batch of five Thai trawlers
will soon be sent to survey marine resources around the island
state in Southern Africa, Dhammarong said.
</P>
<P>
Madagascar is abundant in fishing resources along its 5,000-
mile (8045-kilometers) coastal line, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
