<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Preserves Wetlands with International Aid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, June 12 (Xinhua) -- China has got funding from the
Global Environment Found (GEF) for protecting biodiversity on
four of its wetlands.
</P>
<P>
The five-year wetland preservation project will be implemented
jointly by China and the United Nations Development Program (UNDP),
with 14.28 million US dollars from GEF. It is believed that it is
the first time the GEF has funded a wetland preservation project.
In addition to the funding, GEF will also provide some equipment
and materials for the project.
</P>
<P>
The project aims to find out the best ways to preserve
ecological balance on the wetlands, and the experience may later
be extended to other countries.
</P>
<P>
The four wetlands are: the marshes on the Sanjiang Plain in
Heilongjiang Province, northeast China; the beaches in Yancheng of
Jiangsu Province, east China; the marshes in Dongting Lake in
Hunan Province, central China; and highland marshes on the border
between Sichuan and Gansu provinces, northwest China.
</P>
<P>
The wetland, the forest and the ocean, are the three main
ecosystems on earth. Wetlands are home to a great variety of
plants and animals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
