<HEADLINE> Britain, U.S. Intend to Destabilize Zimbabwe: FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwean Foreign Minister Stan
Mudenge has accused Britain and the United States of teaming up to
sabotage and destabilize Zimbabwe and the whole of southern
Africa, the daily Herald reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Addressing his party's supporters at Mudavanhu secondary school
in Masvingo in south Zimbabwe on Sunday, Mudenge lambasted the
British and American governments, accusing them of trying to
destabilize the region by allegedly sponsoring their puppets to
oust ruling parties.
</P>
<P>
"Today they have targeted Mugabe and the government of the
ruling Zimbabwe African National Union-Patriotic Front, tomorrow
it is going to be Nujoma and his SWAPO (South West Africa People's
Organization) in Namibia, then Mbeki and his African National
Congress in South Africa, and then the whole region," he said.
</P>
<P>
"We are saying no to this whole evil system, and Africa is
prepared to fight back," he said. "We condemn everything they are
doing and if it is going to be a war between blacks and whites, so
let it be."
</P>
<P>
"We know the plots and we are not afraid of them because we
have united as a region to take on the evil system !- the system
that is so evil that let 75 percent of the land in the hands of 1
percent of the population," he said. 
</P>
