</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index ended stable at 2,060 points with a turnover
of 91.2 million NZ dollars (42.7 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Among the leading stocks, WestpacTrust gained 11 cents to 866
cents, Fletcher Energy 10 to 589 cents, Carter Holt Harvey 7 to
197 cents, the Warehouse 6 to 440 cents and Contact Energy 2 to
297 cents.
</P>
<P>
AMP lost 21 cents to 1,990 cents, Tower 15 to 540 cents, Sky TV
14 to 410 cents, Telecom 8 to 773 cents and both Auckland Airport
and Fletcher Paper 1 to 258 and 239 cents respectively.
</P>
<P>
Australia-New Zealand Bank and Fletcher Building closed
unchanged at 1,510 and 218 cents respectively. 
</P>
