<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan is ready to make a
commitment not to be the first to use even conventional arms in
the region if India agrees to do the same, the local newspaper The
News reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
This offer proves Islamabad's sincerity and conviction
regarding the use of force in the subcontinent, Pakistani Chief
Executive General Pervez Musharraf told the press Sunday in Tehran,
capital of Iran, where he is taking part in a regional economic
organization's conference.
