<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Largest Sewage Treatment Plant in SW China Begins Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The largest sewage disposal plant
in western China was put into use recently in Chengdu, the capital
of southwestern Sichuan Province.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the plant, which is capable of handling 300,000
cubic meters of waste water a day, or 40 percent of the city's
total, began three years ago.
</P>
<P>
Located in the southern suburbs of Chengdu, the plant covers an
area of 28.9 hectares. It cost 465 million yuan (about 56 million
U.S. dollars), with 12 million U.S. dollars coming from the
Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
With a population of over three million, the city produces
nearly one million cubic meters of waste water per day.
</P>
<P>
Before the new plant was constructed, 90 percent of the city's
discharged sewage was untreated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
