<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Sixty-four ibis were born in Shaanxi
Province in northwest China since March thanks to the effort of
the Shaanxi Ibis Protection Center on the Qinling Ranges.
</P>
<P>
This has brought the number of the endangered species to over
260 from merely seven in 1981, when it was first found in China.
</P>
<P>
The origin of the bird has been traced back 60 million years,
with large flocks previously found in most of China, Japan, and
Germany. But now the species is found only in China. 
