<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkish President to Attend Assad's Funeral </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Turkish President Ahmet Necdet Sezer
on Monday decided to attend the funeral of late Syrian President
Hafez al-Assad, the first trip abroad for the new president who
took office on May 16 and a move that surprised the observers here.
</P>
<P>
The abrupt decision, announced in a written statement from the
Presidency's press center Monday evening, came in contrast to
Sezer's refusal to attend the just-concluded summit of the 10-
member Economic Cooperation Organization held in Iran.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish Foreign Ministry explained that Sezer's busy
schedule in the early days of his presidency barred him from
leaving the capital.
</P>
<P>
Analysts here said that Sezer's trip to Syria is expected to
have a significant influence on the relations between the two
countries. Sezer will be accompanied by Minister of Culture
Istemihan Talay.
</P>
<P>
Syria and Turkey, which were at odds over security and water-
sharing issues for more than a decade, have remarkably improved
their relations since an agreement was signed in Adana, south
Turkey, in October 1998 on cooperation against terrorism.
</P>
<P>
Turkish State Minister Ramazan Mirzaoglu paid an official visit
to Syria last January. A large business delegation visited Syria
last month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
