<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 12 (Xinhua) -- A memorandum of understanding
for strengthening cooperations among South African, Kenyan and
Ugandan communications departments is being drafted, South African
Communications Ministry announced on Monday.
</P>
<P>
According to Communications Minister Ivy Matsepe-Casaburri, who
has just returned from a five-day working trip to the two east
African countries, the memorandum can serve as the basis for
boosting cooperation in post, telecommunications and broadcasting
sectors to enhance business and investment opportunities.
</P>
<P>
