counterpart W.N. Mudavadi and the Ugandan Minister of Works,
Housing and Communications John Nasasira as "extremely fruitful".
</P>
<P>
Kenya is South Africa's largest trading partner on the
continent, while Uganda is another important economic player.
</P>
<P>
Among key issues to be included in the memorandum are
connectivity in Africa, collaboration between policy-makers and
regulators, rural communication, staff exchange programs, human
resource development and training and postal security. 
