worked was to build an opposition that could bring the ruling
African National Congress below 50 percent of the vote.
</P>
<P>
"It makes no sense for the DP and the NNP to continue fighting
for the support of opposition voters. It is time to put South
Africa first," Leon said.
</P>
<P>
The DP was recognized as the leading opposition party by South
Africans from across the political spectrum.
</P>
<P>
"It makes no sense to give up this clear identity and our
sharply defined message of strong, effective and principled
opposition. It is thus the DP's duty to lead the consolidation of
the opposition," he said. 
