<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canadian, U.S. Firms Merging Into Piping Parts Giant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Prudential Steel Ltd. of Calgary and Missouri-based Maverick
Tube Corp. jointly unveiled their plan Sunday to create the
continent's largest producer of certain "tubular goods and line
pipe for the energy industry," said the report.
</P>
<P>
Under the share swap plan, Maverick shareholders will end up
owning about 53 percent of the combined entity with the remaining
47 percent going to Prudential shareholders.
</P>
<P>
The transaction is expected to close by the third quarter
although the merger is subject to approval from both shareholders
and the Alberta courts.
</P>
<P>
The merged entity, to be named Maverick, will have 2,000
employees. 
</P>
</TEXT>
