<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopian PM Meets Chinese Vice-minister of Foreign Affairs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian Prime Minister Meles
Zenawi Monday exchanged views here with visiting Chinese
Vice-minister of Foreign Affairs Ji Peiding on scheduled "China
and Africa Cooperation Forum", bilateral relations and other
issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Ji briefed Meles on the background and
preparations for the ministerial level forum due to be held in
Beijing on October 10-12.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed appreciation of the Ethiopian government's
support for the meeting, the first of its kind in the history of
Sino-African cooperation.
</P>
<P>
In response, Meles praised China for its timely notification
about the forum, saying that Ethiopia will actively participate in
the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Noting that African countries and China have been sharing
common views on many regional and international issues, Meles
expressed his belief that the relations between African countries
and China will be further strengthened by the forthcoming forum.
</P>
<P>
On the issue of border conflict between Ethiopia and Eritrea,
Ji said the Chinese government has been following the situation
with great concern and advocates to solve the disputes through
dialogue and peaceful means.
</P>
<P>
China is glad to note that the progress has been made in the
recent proximity talks between the two countries sponsored by the
Organization of African Unity (OAU) in Algiers, Ji said.
</P>
<P>
China expects the two countries to make continued cooperation
with the OAU to realize peace and stability in the region, he
added.
</P>
<P>
Ji stressed that as a friendly country to both Ethiopia and
Eritrea and a permanent member of the United Nations Security
Council, China is willing to join hands with the international
community to make efforts to help the two countries realize
political settlement of their conflict.
</P>
<P>
Ji, who arrived here last Saturday, also held talks with
Ethiopian Minister for Economic Development and Cooperation Girma
Biru on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Prior to his meetings with Ethiopian government officials, Ji
met OAU Secretary General Salim Ahmed Salim on Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
