<HEADLINE> Eritrean Colonel Captured by Ethiopia: Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia troops have captured
an Eritrean colonel Gebre-Egziabher Ekubay at the warfront,
according to a report by Ethiopian News Agency on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Gebre-Egziabher, Eritrea's frontiers follow-up logistics head,
was captured at a location between Omhajer and Tessney at the
western front in a counter-offensive launched by Ethiopian troops
last Saturday, the report said.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that by Sunday, fierce fighting between
Ethiopian and Eritrean troops had been continuing at the western
Guluj and eastern Bure fronts although Eritrea had announced to
accept the cessation of hostilities agreement put forward by the
Organization of African Unity. 
</P>
