<HEADLINE> Xinhua Photo List for June 12 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 12 (Xinhua)-- Following is Xinhua's photo list
for June 12:

1. Chinese Vice-Premier Wen Jiabao talks with local farmers in
Bunan County of east China's Anhui province June 11 during his
inspection. Wen urged more efforts to fight against the droughts.

2. Farmers dry honey suckle in Pingyi County of east China's
Shandong province June 12. The county, which is the largest base
of the plant in China, produces over a half of the total honey
suckle in the whole country this year.

3. A girl plays with an elephant in a zoo in Nanning, capital
Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region June 12.

4. Children shake hands with a man dressed as a Japanese cartoon
figure in Mexico City June 10.

5. Chinese Vice-Premier Qian Qichen writes his condolences in a
mourning book over the death of Syrian President Hafez Al-Assad at
the embassy of Syria in Beijing June 12.

6. Chinese President Jiang Zemin shakes hands with President
Festus Mogae of Botswana in Beijing June 12.

7. Policemen in Tibet inspect confiscated hides of wild yaks,
Tibetan antelopes, leopards and otters.

8. The International Fund for China's Environment opens the
Children Environment and Art Educational Base in Xi'an, capital of
northeast China's Shaanxi province, June 12.

9. Zhang Shuhui, a resident in Caoyang District of Beijing, learns
how to deal with gas fire at a "fire-prevention and safety"
training class June 12.

10. Residents in Caoyang district of Beijing learn how to safely
use liquefied petroleum gas at a "fire-prevention and safety"
training class June 12.  
</P>
