<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Qinghua University Receives Donation from Hong Kong Entrepreneur </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Qinghua University, one of China's
most prestigious universities, received 50 million yuan (about six
million U.S. dollars) today from a Hong Kong entrepreneur Chao
Kuang-piu.
</P>
<P>
An official from the university said that the donation will be
used for the construction of a Sports Center.
</P>
<P>
The center is the largest indoor sports center ever constructed
at Qinghua since it was founded almost ninety years ago. The
center, with total investment of 84 million yuan (about ten
million U.S. dollars), will become an important landmark at the
University.
</P>
<P>
Chao Kuang-piu gave financial support to Qinghua University to
develop key scientific and technology projects in 1996 and 1997.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the center is scheduled to be completed in
April 2001.  
</P>
</TEXT>
