<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign Investment Booming In Shandong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Foreign investment in east China's
Shandong Province has increased by 11 percent in the first five
months of the year.
</P>
<P>
According to the Shandong provincial government, in the first
five months, the local government approved the establishment of
889 overseas-funded enterprises with 1.131 billion U.S. dollars in
overseas investments.
</P>
<P>
Of the top 500 multinational corporations in the world, 75 have
invested in the province. There are 12 overseas-funded projects
with overseas investment amounting to over 100 million U.S.
dollars each.  
</P>
</TEXT>
