<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Geared To Attract More Talent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, the biggest economic
and commercial city in China, will adopt new measures to attract
talented people from home and abroad, a senior official from
Shanghai Municipal People's Government said here today.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai will continue to offer preferential policies to
attract talent from all over the globe, especially those who are
well versed in IT technology, finance, insurance and other hi-tech
industries, the official said at an international workshop on
human resources held here today.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, Shanghai employed some 7,000
talented personnel in China last year, up 2,000 compared to the
previous year.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Municipal People's Government gives top priority
to the development of human resources. It has abolished residence
registration for talented personnel, the official said.
</P>
<P>
He also said that some new websites for human resources and an
international human resource market will be established soon.
</P>
</TEXT>
