<BODY>
<HEADLINE> No Deaths Reported in Tibetan Landslide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lhasa, June 12 (Xinhua) -- No deaths have been reported on the
June 10 landslide in eastern Tibet as all residents near the scene
of the landslide have been rushed to safe areas, local media
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The landslide occurred in Yigong Township in Bomi County on
April 9, destroying seven kilometers of highways, blocking the
Yigong River and leaving more than 4,000 residents homeless.
</P>
<P>
The water level of the river-turned Lake has continued to rise
despite a ditch diverting water from the blocked river dug out by
local soldiers and civilians with the help of a team of engineers
dispatched by the State Flood Control Headquarters.
</P>
<P>
On June 8, high temperature led to the melting of a
considerable amount of ice and snow in the nearby mountains. The
water level of the lake rose dramatically.
</P>
<P>
On the evening of June 10, the torrent waters from the lake
completely destroyed the ditch. Nearby roads, bridges and
telecommunications facilities were damaged.
</P>
<P>
The local government immediately took measures to evacuate all
residents in potential flood areas.
</P>
<P>
The water level of the lake and nearby rivers has receded.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
