<HEADLINE> India Permits 100 Percent FDI in Refining, E-Commerce </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The decision to remove the 49 percent ceiling on FDI in oil
refining and E-Commerce was taken at a meeting of the cabinet
chaired by Prime Minister Atal Bihari Vajpayee, Parliamentary
Affairs Minister Pramod Mahajan said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the government also abolished the 15 billion rupees
(3.49 billion U.S. dollars) limit in power as part of efforts to
boost private participation in infrastructure sectors.
</P>
<P>
In the case of power sector, where 100 percent FDI already
allowed through automatic route, the ceiling of 15 billion rupees
has been done away for generation, transmission and distribution.
</P>
<P>
As a further step to boost FDI flow, the government also
removed the condition of export earnings by foreign companies to
compensate the dividend repatriated to parent companies. 
