<HEADLINE> Science, Education Top Priority for China's Western Development: Li </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Chinese vice premier Li Lanqing
has stressed the importance of science, technology and education
reforms in developing western China.
</P>
<P>
Li, also a member of the standing committee of the Chinese
Communist Party central committee, made these remarks during his
four-day inspection tour of Chongqing, the largest industrial city
in west China.
</P>
<P>
Li said further educational reforms are needed to produce all
kinds of professionals for the ongoing massive development in
China's west.
</P>
<P>
Structural reforms in science and technology industry should be
deepened so that science and technology can play a vital role in
developing China's western regions.
</P>
<P>
During his discussions with presidents and directors of
universities and research institutions in the city, Li said
measures should be taken to foster talented personnel.
</P>
<P>
It is of great importance for the improvement of educational
and the realization of developing goals in western development
that nine-year compulsory education is made available to all the
school-age children, and illiteracy among youths and adults is
eradicated, Li said. The central government and local governments
should continue to support education in the west. Schools in
eastern China should help schools in poverty-stricken areas to
improve working conditions and the quality of teaching.
</P>
<P>
Li also talked about the importance of promoting Medicare
reforms.
</P>
<P>
Among those accompanying the vice-premier during his visit were
Education Minister Chen Zhili and Science and Technology Minister
Zhu Lilan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
