<HEADLINE> Capital Market to Spur Development In Western China (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, June 12 (Xinhua) -- China plans to foster an active
capital market as part of a national campaign on developing the
country's western area.
</P>
<P>
"The central government is looking into a number of policies to
support the formation and development of the western capital
market," said Gan Fangqian, deputy director of the Regional
Economic Development Department of the State Development Planning
Commission (SDPC), at an International Symposium on developing
China's western region today.
</P>
<P>
Chinese officials of the western region participating in the
symposium said they are taking measures to enhance the ability of
local financial institutions in collecting funds, draw more idle
funds to develop the economy, and encourage more high-tech
companies to be listed on the stock market.
</P>
<P>
"As the largest city in western China, Chongqing is encouraging
more overseas financial institutions to set up business offices
here, setting up regional commercial banks, raising the amount of
funds collected by banks, and making social assets more active,"
said Wang Hongju, vice-mayor of Chongqing Municipality.
</P>
<P>
Western Chinese provinces and Chongqing can collect funds
through local banks, lotteries, and other kinds of funds, said
Zhang Hanya, director of the Investment Research Institute of the
SDPC.
</P>
<P>
A paper presented by the Chinese Academy of Social Sciences (
CASS) at the Symposium suggests that a long-term bond exchange
should be set up in western China to raise funds.
</P>
</TEXT>
