<HEADLINE> Malaysia Airlines, Mid-East Airlines to Begin Code Share Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia Airlines (MAS) and
Middle East Airlines will begin code-sharing effective Friday on
flights operated by MAS between Beirut, Lebanon and Sydney via
Kuala Lumpur, according to a MAS statement Monday.
</P>
<P>
With the signing of the code-share agreement held Monday in
Beirut, the statement said Middle East Airlines would get a seat
allocation on MAS' services between Beirut and Kuala Lumpur and
vice-versa and between Beirut and Sydney and vice-versa.
</P>
<P>
"Malaysia Airlines on the other hand will be able to operate
additional services to Beirut," it said.
</P>
<P>
The code-sharing will initially be on a twice weekly frequency
and will be increased to thrice weekly effective on July 19 when
MAS commences its third service to Beirut.
</P>
<P>
Through this cooperation, both airlines will strengthen their
position in the market between Lebanon and Australia besides
continuing to promote travel between Malaysia and Lebanon, it said.
</P>
<P>
This is another step taken by MAS to further promote the Kuala
Lumpur International Airport (KLIA) as a regional hub, the
statement added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
