<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Announces One Day Mourning for Assad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladeshi government has
decided to observe a mourning day Tuesday for late Syrian
president Hafez Al Assad, said an official handout Monday.
</P>
<P>
The government also announced that national flags would be
flown at half-mast atop all governmental, semi-governmental and
autonomous organizations to mark the day, the handout said.
</P>
<P>
Syrian President Hafez Al Assad died of heart attack on
Saturday. Bangladeshi Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina expressed her
profound shock at the demise of Assad Saturday in a message of
condolence.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister, accompanied by State Minister for Foreign
Affairs Abul Hasan Chowdhury and Foreign Secretary C.M. Shafi Sami,
leaves Dhaka Monday evening for Damascus to attend the funeral of
the late Syrian president.
</P>
<P>
The funeral will be held Tuesday at his village home of
Qarddaha, 200 kilometers northwest of Damascus. 
</P>
