<HEADLINE> Daily Report on Quality of Air in Key Chinese Cities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Taiyuan in north China's Shanxi
Province suffered slight air pollution today, while the air in
Shijiazhuang, Shenyang and Wuhan was somewhat polluted.
</P>
<P>
The report, issued by the China Environmental Monitoring Center,
said that Beijing, Tianjin, Hohhot, Dalian, Changchun, Harbin,
Shanghai, Nanjing, Suzhou, Nantong, Hangzhou, Wenzhou, Hefei,
Nanchang, Jinan, Qingdao, Yantai, Zhengzhou, Changsha, Zhanjiang,
Chongqing, Guiyang, Kunming, Lhasa, Xi'an, Lanzhou and Xining
enjoyed fairly good air.
</P>
<P>
Excellent air was reported in Fuzhou, Xiamen, Guangzhou,
Shenzhen, Zhuhai, Shantou, Nanning, Haikou, Chengdu, Yinchuang and
Urumqi.
</P>
<P>
Beijing, Tianjin, Shenyang, Dalian, Harbin, Shanghai, Nanjing,
Suzhou, Hangzhou, Xi'an, and 18 other cities listed absorbable
suspended particles as the major pollutants, while sulfur dioxide
was the major pollutant in Chongqing, Guiyang and Kunming.
</P>
<P>
The 42 cities include China's four municipalities directly
under the central government, the provincial and regional capitals
and 10 major coastal cities.  
</P>
</TEXT>
