Award and Nepali Film Festival will be held here on July 7-9, the
Radio Nepal reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
A total of 34 of the best Nepali movies released between
January 1, 1997 to mid-April, 2000 will compete for 27 different
awards, including Best Film, Best Male and Female Actors and Best
Song, among others, the radio said.
</P>
<P>
Foreign film producers and film artists, including Indian
actress Jaya Pradha and Pooja Batra as well as Bangladeshi actress
Rojina,will also attend the festival, it said.
</P>
