<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-U.S. Work Safety Center Founded in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Libery Mutual Safe Work Center, a
Sino-U.S. joint research project, has been set up in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The center will carry out research on prevention of occupation
diseases and industrial accidents, and rehabilitation of the
injured and disabled. It is to provide related training and
consulting service, and recommend feasible production safety
programs to the local enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The center was founded by the Medical School of Fudan
University (MSFU) in Shanghai and Libery Mutual Research Center of
U.S. (LMRC).
</P>
<P>
Liang Youxin, professor with MSFU, said that due to work
pressure and intense competition, people are more likely to suffer
occupation diseases and accidents at work.
</P>
<P>
Officials with LMRC said that the center is great importance to
Shanghai, the biggest city in China with all types of occupations.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that over 100,000 are killed in accidents every
year in China during the past few years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
