<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fresh Clash in Indonesia's Maluku Province Kills Four </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Four persons were killed and six
others injured as fresh communal clashes broke out in Ambon,
capital of Indonesia's Maluku province.
</P>
<P>
According to the Antara News Agency, the clash broke out on
Monday morning when a group of villagers from Wara and Aster
Tantui attacked those in Hative Kecil Atas village in Sirimau
subdistrict.
</P>
<P>
An angry mob also torched six houses in the village.
</P>
<P>
The fight was broken up by members of the police's mobile
brigade and the marines. The situation in the village has returned
to calm as security personnel continue to patrol the area.
</P>
<P>
There was no further information on the reason for the attack,
Antara said.
</P>
<P>
Maluku has witnessed a year-long ethnic bloodshed between
Christians and Muslims, which has claimed more than 1,300 civilian
lives. Clashes have subsided in recent months but tension remains
high in some areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
