<HEADLINE> French FM Says No Need to Worry About Future of Syria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 12 (Xinhua) -- French Foreign Minister Hubert
Vedrine said Monday that there is no particular reason to worry
about the future of Syria after the death of President Hafez Assad.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with radio and television Europe 1, Vedrine
said that he does not see any particular threat to the stability
of Syria, although there exist some uncertainties.
</P>
<P>
He said that the change of generation in the leadership of
Syria would also bring about a "change of conception and thinking.
"
</P>
<P>
"Therefore, one can pose questions but there is no reason to
worry," he added.
</P>
<P>
The French foreign minister also said that he expects the
Middle East peace process to continue because President Assad had
agreed to look for a peace settlement with Israel on the condition
that it should be just. 
</P>
