<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ICBC Gives Full Support to Development of Western Regions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The Industrial and Commercial Bank
of China (ICBC) will give full support to the development of the
less developed areas in West China, said Jiang Jianqing, president
of the ICBC.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said today that the ICBC will focus its support on
infrastructural construction in western provinces, especially
projects in transportation, electric power transmission networks,
telecommunications, energy, water and gas supply that have been
listed in the state's overall development plan.
</P>
<P>
He said that the ICBC has always given financial support to the
economic development of western areas. In 1998 the ICBC provided
loans of 9.05 billion yuan (about 1.15 billion U.S. dollars) to
finance 18 projects in highways, urban electric power supply
projects, urban construction and telecommunications projects in
western areas.
</P>
<P>
In 1999, the ICBC further stepped up its support to
infrastructural construction in western areas, and at the same
time channeled more loans to technological remolding and high-tech
projects of key enterprises in these areas, ratifying 104 projects
so far with loans of 6.7 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
He said that this year the ICBC will continue to support
infrastructural construction in western areas, and will readjust
its loaning policies according to the characteristics of different
projects.  
</P>
</TEXT>
