<HEADLINE> CNPC and Agip Sign Oil Contract </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 12 (Xinhua) The China National Petroleum Corp (
CNPC) and the Italian Agip Oil Company has signed cooperation
contract for exploring oil and gas in the Sebei Block in west
China's Qaidam Basin, according to today's China Petroleum News.
</P>
<P>
Some six natural gas fields with verified gas reserves totaling
13.404 million cubic meters have so far been discovered in the
Sebei Block which covers a total area of 6,998.4 square kilometers.
</P>
<P>
According to the contract, Agip will be investor and operator
and is expected to complete the exploratory work within the
contract period.
</P>
<P>
The paper said that Agip has all along been active in
developing China's onshore oil resources, which has so far
undertaken five oil projects in west China's Tarim Basin and in
east China's Bohai Sea.  
</P>
</TEXT>
