<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Urges Cultural Advancement in Western Region </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 12 (Xinhua) -- China's Ministry of Culture
recently urged localities to do more for promoting cultural
advancement in the country's western region.
</P>
<P>
The ministry will provide special funds for constructing
cultural facilities in rural areas, such as libraries, museums,
movie theaters and cultural centers, the People's Daily reported
today.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the ministry plans to organize well-known writers
and artists to plunge themselves to the thick of life in the west,
the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
The writers and artists are asked to create more excellent
works for describing the real lives of the western region.
</P>
<P>
The ministry warns of damage of cultural relics during the
economic development in the region.
</P>
<P>
All the local heritage administrations are called on to make
comprehensive arrangements for well maintaining treasured relics
and cultural ruins in the western region, especially the areas
mainly populated by ethnic minorities, the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
The State Administration of Cultural Heritage this year will
focus on excavation projects in the Three Gorges areas and the
Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, the newspaper said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
