<HEADLINE> URGENT Clinton-Arafat Meeting Postponed to Thursday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GAZA, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The scheduled Wednesday meeting
between U.S. President Bill Clinton and Chairman of the Palestinian
National Authority Yasser Arafat in Washington has been postponed
to Thursday, a senior Palestinian official said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
According to an advisor to Arafat, the one-day delay is because
that both Arafat and U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright
will attend Tuesday's funeral of the late Syrian President Hafez
al-Assad, who died of heart attack last Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Arafat will meet Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak Monday to
discuss the latest developments of the Middle East peace process,
in the light of Assad's death and the expected resumption of
Israeli-Palestinian peace negotiations in Washington.
</P>
<P>
Following his meeting with Mubarak, Arafat will leave for Syria
to attend Assad's funeral. 
</P>
