<HEADLINE> China's First Job-Seeking Website for Graduates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Chinese university graduates
encounter difficulties in seeking work due to a lack of employment
information. But now they have a way out.
</P>
<P>
The opening of China's first job-seeking website --www.9989.net-
- will make it easier for them to get over the difficulties.
</P>
<P>
The website, founded by some postgraduates from Nanjing
University aims to collect and provide information for local
university graduates and employers. In addition, it also provides
information for overseas companies.
</P>
<P>
The website can help reduce costs of both employers and job-
seekers while serving as a new communicating channel between them.
</P>
<P>
The website has registered 2,000 students from local
universities looking for jobs. 
