<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Major Inter-Korean Agreements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The following is a list of major
inter-Korean agreements reached in the past two decades.
</P>
<P>
July 4, 1972 -- South-North Joint Communique, agreeing on the
three unification principles -- independence, peace and grand
national unity.
</P>
<P>
November 4, 1972 -- Agreement on the Formation and Operation of
a South-North Coordinating Committee.
</P>
<P>
August 22, 1985 -- Agreement on Exchange Visits by Separated
Family Members and Art Troupes.
</P>
<P>
July 26, 1990 -- Agreement on South-North High-level Meeting.
</P>
<P>
December 13, 1991 -- Agreement on reconciliation, non-
aggression, and exchange and cooperation, known as the "Basic
Agreement."
</P>
<P>
December 13, 1991 -- Joint Agreement on the Denuclearization of
the Korean Peninsula.
</P>
<P>
February 7, 1992 -- Agreement on the Composition and Operation
of Subcommittees for High-level Talks.
</P>
<P>
March 14, 1992 -- Agreement on the Establishment and Operation
of a South-North Joint Nuclear Control Commission.
</P>
<P>
May 17, 1992 -- Agreement on the Establishment and Operation of
a South-North Military Commission.
</P>
<P>
May 17, 1992 -- Agreement on the Establishment and Operation of
South-North Joint Commissions for Exchange and Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
May 17, 1992 -- Agreement on the Establishment and Operation of
South-North Liaison Office.
</P>
<P>
June 28, 1994 -- Agreement on South-North Summit Talks in
Pyongyang on July 25-27. The two sides reached the agreement on
procedural matters, including the formation and size of a
delegation, the format of talks, the itinerary, contacts between
working-level officials and the dispatch of an advance team.
</P>
<P>
July 2,1994 -- Agreement on Procedural Matters for South-North
Summit Talks.
</P>
<P>
June 3, 1999 -- Agreement on the South-North Vice Minister-
Level Talks.
</P>
<P>
April 8,2000 --- Agreement on South-North Summit Talks signed
in Beijing, China. The two sides agreed to convene a South-North
summit in Pyongyang on June 12-14 via secret contacts between
authorities.
</P>
<P>
May 18, 2000 -- Agreement on Procedural Matters to Implement
the South-North Agreement for the Pyongyang Summit. The two sides
reached the agreement on the forthcoming of a delegation, the
format of talks, agenda, transport, etc. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
