<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic News Summary at 0500 GMT, June 12 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A report from the ministry said the Swedish government had
cooperated with the Thai government in organizing a seminar, which
will be held here Monday, aiming to brainstorm ideas from all
parties concerned to tailor a master plan on development
approaches of the island of Phuket, 862 kilometers south of
Bangkok. (Thailand-Sweden-Cyber Port)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- India's inflation rate shot up to 6.59 percent for
the week ended on May 27, as primary food article prices continued
an upward climb for the second consecutive week.
</P>
<P>
According to the Reserve Bank of India, the inflation rate,
calculated on the basis of Wholesale Price Index, rose by 0.29
percentage points during the week to 6.59 percent from 6.30
percent in the previous week and 3.11 percent a year ago.
</P>
<P>
The country's inflation rate touched a whopping 6.75 percent on
April 1, 2000. (India-Inflation)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BANGKOK -- The Thai government will not start to repay the
bailout loan it received from the International Monetary Fund (IMF)
during the economic crisis before schedule, Prime Minister Chuan
Leekpai was quoted by Thai News Agency as saying Sunday.
</P>
<P>
"The government had yet talked about the issue, but had decided
to stop to withdraw further funds from the IMF's rescue package,"
he said. (Thailand-IMF-Loan) 
</P>
