<HEADLINE> Sweden Backs Thailand to Build Cyber Port </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The Swedish government supports
the Thai government's plan to develop the country's renowned
southern resort of Phuket into a cyber port and international city,
the Thai Ministry of Science, Technology and Environment said here
Monday.
</P>
<P>
A report from the ministry said the Swedish government had
cooperated with the Thai government in organizing a seminar, which
will be held here Monday, aiming to brainstorm ideas from all
parties concerned to tailor a master plan on development
approaches of the island of Phuket, 862 kilometers south of
Bangkok.
</P>
<P>
The Swedish government also expressed its willingness to
support the Thai government in respect of both the technology
knowhow and expertise necessary to help achieve the goal,
according to the report. 
</P>
