<HEADLINE> Pacers Beat Lakers in Game Three of NBA Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Indiana Pacers point guard
Reggie Miller scored 33 points and Jalen Rose 21 in Game 3 of the
NBA Finals Sunday evening as the Los Angeles Lakers was beaten 100-
91 with second superstar Kobe Bryant sat out following an injured
left ankle two nights earlier.
</P>
<P>
The Pacers also used the notorious "Hack-a-Shaq" strategy in
the fourth quarter, and this time the strategy paid off for the
Pacers as MVP Shaquille O'Neal scored 33 points but made only 3-of-
13 from the free throw line.
</P>
<P>
Even so, the Lakers, who never led, crept within 3 points on a
Ron Harper 3-pointer with 14 seconds to go, following an O'Neal
offensive rebound.
</P>
<P>
"If we were down 3-0 you could have pretty much written us off.
We needed a gutty effort and we got it." said Miller, who made
four free throws in the end of the game.
</P>
<P>
The Lakers not only missed Bryant's scoring in Game 3. He is
also an aggressive force on defense and a good rebounder.
</P>
<P>
Bryant, a second-team All-NBA selection as well as first-team
all-defense pick, was injured while making his only shot of Game 2
on Friday night, a 17-foot jumper with 3:26 left in the first
quarter.
</P>
<P>
The Lakers missed Bryant's offense Sunday evening, getting just
six points from Brian Shaw, his replacement in the starting lineup.
</P>
<P>
Bryant is believed to have two more full days off before Game 4,
to be played Wednesday night, but the Lakers coach Phil Jackson
acknowledged, "Realistically speaking, Kobe won't be 100 percent
for a while." That means he might miss Game 4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
