<DOCNO> XIE20000612.0595 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NBA Downgrades O'Neal's Flagrant To Personal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The NBA agreed to the Los
Angeles center Shaquille O'Neal complain and announced Sunday,
hours before Game 3 of the Finals in Indianapolis, that a flagrant
foul called on the MVP in Game 2 of the NBA Finals Friday night
was downgraded to a personal foul.
</P>
<P>
O'Neal had said he did not understand how a wall could be
called a flagrant offender when a sports car runs into it.
</P>
<P>
"When a little guy in a sports car runs into a brick wall they
call a flagrant foul. I never did understand the rule but I guess
I'm big and I can take it," O'Neal said.
</P>
<P>
O'Neal was assessed a flagrant foul for a hard rejection of
point guard Travis Best on a drive with 6:40 to go in the game,
which the Lakers won 111-104 to take a 2-0 lead over the Indiana
Pacers in the best-of-seven series.
</P>
<P>
There was plenty of body contact, but O'Neal also got his hand
on the ball, and the flagrancy of the foul was doubtful,
especially since it was debatable which player initiated contact.
</P>
<P>
The foul was O'Neal's fifth of the game -- one short of fouling
out -- and coach Phil Jackson sat him down for about a minute as
Indiana capitalized by scoring four points on the foul shots and
ball possession that comes with a flagrant foul.
</P>
<P>
Rescinding that flagrant call could be significant should O'
Neal be called for another. A player is automatically suspended
one game after his fourth flagrant foul point. A player gets one
point for a flagrant foul 1 and two points for a flagrant foul 2.
</P>
<P>
The Lakers coach Phil Jackson said the league decision had
removed the possibility that O'Neal "would get an accidental one (
flagrant foul) or something that we consider not aggressive or
nonflagrant in that same situation" and miss a Finals game.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
