<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Private Community Services Emerging in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Private community services are
booming in Tianjin, according to a survey by civil affairs
departments.
</P>
<P>
The survey showed that private service companies in some
districts account for two-thirds of the total community service
companies in the port city.
</P>
<P>
Private community service companies offer many services to
local citizens and are more flexible in providing help than state-
owned ones, the survey showed. Their major services include house
calls by doctors, delivering goods and providing cleaning and
domestic services.
</P>
<P>
"We are making efforts to win the trust of residents by
providing high-quality services instead of advertisements," said
Wang Yuxiang, director of a local private service company.
</P>
<P>
Private community services have provided more employment
opportunities for the laid-offs. At the same time, state-owned
service companies are compelled to improve the quality of their
services in the face of stiff competition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
