<HEADLINE> Cataract Sufferers Benefit from Sino-US Founded Ophthalmology Clinic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The Sino-U.S. founded the Boai
Ophthalmology Clinic in the northern port city of Tianjin has
presented about 2,000 man-made crystalline lens to cataract
sufferers since it was established five years ago.
</P>
<P>
The clinic has helped 20,000 cataract sufferers regain eyesight
with crystalline lens transplant operation with equipment and
expertise from the U.S. The patients are between six months and
96 years of age.
</P>
<P>
China has 40,000,000 cataract sufferers, 4,000,000 of whom are
blind. 
