<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Doctoral Thesis of Famous Chinese Writer to Be Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The doctoral thesis of a famous
Chinese writer Qian Zhongshu will be published soon by the Daxiang
Publishing House.
</P>
<P>
"China Depicted In British Literature During The 17th and 18th
Centuries," the doctoral thesis in English, has been rarely
researched by modern scholars so far, the Shanghai-based Wenhui
Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
The thesis is divided into three parts and covers a large
corpus of material concerning China found in British literary
works in the 17th and 18th centuries.
</P>
<P>
Qian wrote the thesis in English with many French, German and
Latin quotations, when applying for an associate doctorate in the
English Faculty at Oxford University in the late 1930s.
</P>
<P>
Qian spent most of his life researching Chinese and Western
Literature. He died in 1998, leaving behind a legacy of works
admired by Chinese and foreigners.
</P>
<P>
His famous works include "Fortress Besieged," which has been
translated into dozens of foreign languages. 
</P>
</TEXT>
