<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA -- The six-day Fighting between Rwandan and Ugandan
forces in Kisangani in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC)
ceased Sunday, Zambian President Frederick Chiluba said here.
</P>
<P>
He said the two warring countries have agreed to stop fighting
and that their troops have withdrawn one kilometer away from where
they were fighting.
</P>
<P>
The military chiefs of the two warring countries reached the
agreement on stopping their fighting in the DRC's northeastern
city of Kisangani, said Chiluba, who went to Uganda and Rwanda on
Saturday and held consultations respectively with Ugandan
President Yoweri Museveni and Rwandan President Paul Kagame on how
to stop the fighting.  (Rwanda-Uganda-Ceasefire)
