<HEADLINE> International Machinery, Electronic Product Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Wuhan, capital of central China's
Hubei Province, will hold an international machinery and
electronic products fair from September 23-26.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, the fair will have an exhibition
floor space of 12,000 sq. m., including 500 indoor business booths
with a combined area of 8,000 sq. m.
</P>
<P>
Commodities displayed will include textile, agricultural and
food machinery, home appliances, computers, automobiles spare
parts, ship and boat equipment, as well as medical and sport
equipment. A number of seminars and trade talks will also be held
to promote exchanges and negotiations on new technologies, new
products and overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
Wuhan, the largest comprehensive industrial base in central
China with a population of 7.6 million, has seen increasing export
of machinery products in recent years. Last year, the export of
machinery and electronic products topped for the first time 400
million U.S. dollars.  
</P>
