<HEADLINE> Innovation Stressed in Space Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 12 (Xinhua) -- China should actively promote
technological innovation and development of its space technology
if the country hopes to retain its lead in the area, a leading
expert said.
</P>
<P>
At a recent symposium, Shen Rongjun, a pioneer in China's space
survey and control network, said that after 40 years, the country
has succeeded in building up a complete and unique space network.
</P>
<P>
Successes are due in no small part to the innovation of Chinese
scientists who blazed a number of new trails, said Shen.
</P>
<P>
The space network has also encouraged the development of China'
s light science, telecommunications and information technology,
bringing huge economic and social benefits to the country, added
Shen. 
</P>
</TEXT>
