<HEADLINE> Britain's McRay Wins Greece's 47th Acropolis Rally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Britain's Collin McRay, 31, Sunday
won the 47th Acropolis rally in Greece after defeating Spain's
Carlos Sainz, who was in second place.
</P>
<P>
Juha Kankounen from Finland came third.
</P>
<P>
A total of 117 drivers participated in the four-day race which
began Friday morning from the foot of the ancient Acropolis and
covered 1,408 kilometers through central Greece.
</P>
<P>
The Acropolis rally, which was considered one of the toughest
in the world, counts toward the world driving championship.
</P>
</TEXT>
